SIMPLE: hike
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hike
<hw>Hike</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Hiked</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Hiking</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. <er>Hitch</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To move with a swing, toss, throw, jerk, or the
like.</def> <mark>[Dial. or Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To raise with a quick movement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To raise (a price) quickly or significantly in a
single step.</def> <illu>They <ex>hiked</ex> gasoline prices twenty
cents in less than a week.</illu>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Football)</fld> <def>To pass (the ball) from the
center to the quarterback at the start of the play; to <er>snap</er>
(the ball).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hike</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Hike
<hw>Hike</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To hike
one's self; specif., to go with exertion or effort; to tramp; to march
laboriously.</def> <mark>[Dial. or Colloq.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧If you persist
in heaving and <xex>hiking</xex> like this.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Kipling.</au></rj></p>

<p><q>It's <qex>hike</qex>, <qex>hike</qex>, <qex>hike</qex> (march)
till you stick in the mud, and then you <qex>hike</qex> back again a
little slower than you went.</q> <rj><qau>Scribner's Mag.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>to take a long walk, especially for pleasure or
exercise.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hike</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Hike
<hw>Hike</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
hiking.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A long walk usually for exercise or pleasure or
exercise; a tramp; a march.</def> <wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><q>With every <qex>hike</qex> there's a few laid out with their hands
crossed.</q> <rj><qau>Scribner's Mag.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>an increase in cost, rate, etc.; <as>as, there was a
dramatic <ex>hike</ex> in gasoline prices; a <ex>hike</ex> in the
interest rates</as>.</def> <wns>[wns=2]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> rise, boost.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <def>the amount a salary is
increased; <as>as, he got a wage <ex>hike</ex></as>.</def>
<wns>[wns=3]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> raise, rise.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hilal</ent>⟦br⟧
